Unfortunately, the fix for bug 1016165 is incomplete. The clamping operation[2] introduced in the
patch works correctly most of the time. However, it takes the upper bound as a single-precision
parameter, whereas the buffer size is calculated based on the double-precision `max_delay_time_`
variable. As a result, the clamped value might end up about 1e-5 larger than `max_delay_time_`. If
the sample rate is high enough, this will allow `read_index1` in [3] to become less than zero (-2 in
the provided test case).


